Yakubu Dogara is under investigation by the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission over allegations he illegally added figures to Nigeria&#8217;s 2016 budget. ABUJA Nigeria s anti-corruption agency is investigating the speaker of the lower chamber of parliament, according to a document seen by Reuters on Monday, part of a campaign against graft being waged by President Muhammadu Buhari s government.Yakubu Dogara, the speaker of the House of Representatives, is under investigation by the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission over allegations he illegally added figures to Nigeria s 2016 budget after it was passed by parliament, according to a letter from the watchdog dated 9 June and seen by Reuters.A spokesman for Dogara did not respond to repeated calls for comment.Buhari won the presidency on promises to combat Nigeria s endemic corruption. But halfway through his four-year term, the results have been mixed, and one of his own senior advisors was suspended after a Senate investigation into embezzlement.